webpackJsonp([0xf03ae30fed],{4473:function(a,n){a.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<h1><code>instanceof</code> operator</h1>\n<p>The <code>instanceof</code> operator allows you to check the validity of a <code>IS A</code> relationship. If at any point of time, we are not sure about this and we want to validate this at runtime, we can do the following:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-java"><code><span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">//assuming vehicle is an instance of Class `Car` the expression inside the \'if\' will  return true</span>\n<span class="token keyword">if</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>vehicle <span class="token keyword">instanceof</span> <span class="token class-name">Car</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n    <span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">//do something if vehicle is a Car</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p> <strong>Note</strong>: If you apply the instanceof operator with any variable that has null value, it returns false.</p>',fields:{slug:"/java/instanceof-operator/"},frontmatter:{title:"instanceof Operator"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/java/instanceof-operator/"}}}});
